cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 85 miles NNE of Grand Cayman
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to cross central Cuba tonight, then move north-northeast toward the Florida Keys and extreme south-Florida on Sunday, before turning northwest and then west into the south-central Gulf of Mexico early next week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near the Florida Keys / extreme south-Florida coast

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical-storm watch in effect from north of Jupiter Inlet to the Brevard/Volusia County line and from north of Bonita Beach to Englewood (central-south FL coasts)
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical-storm warning from Jupiter Inlet southward around the peninsula to Bonita Beach including Lake Okeechobee and the Florida Keys; Hurricane watch Deerfield Beach to Bonita Beach and Keys; Storm-surge watch Golden Beach to Bonita Beach and Keys
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Central Cuba, the NW Bahamas, South Florida peninsula and Keys, then portions of the eastern Gulf coast
weather_observation.wind: Low chance (<10%) of tropical-storm-force gusts; breezy conditions possible mid-week as Eta lingers in the Gulf
weather_observation.storm_surge: NWS surge graphic indicates 2–3 ft possible from the Flagler/Volusia County Line northward to Altamaha Sound, which includes the Jacksonville coast
weather_observation.rainfall: Occasional rain bands could bring 1–2 inches through mid-week; widespread 4-inch totals are not expected this far north
weather_observation.other_hazards: Increased rip-current risk and minor coastal flooding during high tides
